OL,6,FLater on in the footage, which was
OL,7,Fcaptured by police officers' body-worn
OL,8,Fcameras, Mrs Rawle said: "He will come
OL,9,Fand get me. If he gets well, he will
OL,10,Fcome and get me and he will kill me.
OL,12,F"The constant threats, the constant
OL,13,Fundermining, the constant laughing
OL,14,Fbehind my back. I would have taken my
OL,15,Fown life."
OL,17,FMrs Rawle is then told by an officer
OL,18,Fthat her husband has died and is
OL,19,Farrested on suspicion of murder.
