OL,6,FThe couple can be heard insulting each
OL,7,Fother and rowing about money, alcohol,
OL,8,Ftheir children and their marriage.
OL,10,F"Every day I've got to work while you
OL,11,Fsit there getting fat," Mr Rawle says.
OL,13,F"You don't do anything now. I have got
OL,14,Fto work to support you. Why else do I
OL,15,Fgo to work?"
OL,17,FMrs Rawle tells her husband she had
OL,18,Fbeen ill and accuses him of being a
OL,19,F"liar and a narcissist".
